# Basemap PMTiles archive served at runtime via HTTP range requests.
# Local development defaults to the Italy extract in studio/public/italia.pmtiles
# (served by Vite at /italia.pmtiles). Leave unset to use that default.
# In production, point this at the self-hosted Italy extract on Cloudflare R2, e.g.:
#   VITE_TILES_URL=https://tiles.zornade.com/italia.pmtiles
# VITE_TILES_URL=/italia.pmtiles

# --- Access gate -------------------------------------------------------------
#
# There are TWO sets of variables. Do not mix them up.
#
# A) PRODUCTION (Netlify Functions, the robust path). Set these in the Netlify
#    UI → Site settings → Environment variables. NOTE: NO "VITE_" prefix — these
#    are read server-side by netlify/functions and must never reach the browser.
#      STUDIO_USER=redazione
#      STUDIO_PASS_SHA256=<hex sha-256 of the password>
#      STUDIO_SESSION_SECRET=<long random string, e.g. `openssl rand -hex 32`>
#
# B) LOCAL DEV fallback (plain `vite` without functions). Put these in a
#    gitignored .env.local. WITH the "VITE_" prefix (exposed to the client).
#      VITE_STUDIO_USER=redazione
#      VITE_STUDIO_PASS_SHA256=<hex sha-256 of the password>
#
# Generate the hash by typing your password yourself in a terminal:
#   printf '%s' 'LA_TUA_PASSWORD' | sha256sum
